Chthonius lanai

n. sp.
differs from 

C. italicus

in the following characters: anterior eyes reduced to a smooth cuticular area (no eyes in 

C. italicus

); chaetotaxy of tergites I–IV 2:2–3:4:4 [(2–3)4:3–4:4: 
4 in

C. italicus

]; fixed chelal finger straight (slightly curved in 

C. italicus

); fixed and movable chelal fingers with larger and more widely spaced teeth (
Figs 305–307
) [with smaller and more close-set teeth (
Figs 275–277, 279–281
) in 

C. italicus

].
